https://leetcode.com/problems/find-the-smallest-divisor-given-a-threshold/solutions/?orderBy=most_votes

Input: nums = [1,2,5,9], threshold = 6
Output: 5

Input: nums = [44,22,33,11,1], threshold = 5
Output: 44

Explanation
Binary search the result.
If the sum > threshold, the divisor is too small.
If the sum <= threshold, the divisor is big enough.

int smallestDivisor(vector<int>& A, int threshold) {
    int left = 1, right = 1e6, m, sum;
    while (left < right) {
        m = (left + right) / 2, sum = 0;
        for (int i : A)
            sum += (i + m - 1) / m;
        if (sum > threshold)
            left = m + 1;
        else
            right = m;
    }
    return left;
}

Complexity
Time O(NlogM), where M = max(A)
Space O(1)
